solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    int lengthOfLongestSubstring(string s) {
        vector<int> last(256, -1);
        int left = 0, maxLen = 0;
        for (int right = 0; right < s.size(); ++right) {
            unsigned char c = s[right];
            if (last[c] >= left) left = last[c] + 1;
            last[c] = right;
            maxLen = max(maxLen, right - left + 1);
        }
        return maxLen;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Sliding-window with a fixed-size array to store the last index of each character. The window expands rightward and contracts leftward only when a duplicate is found, ensuring each character is processed once.

